com.sailpoint.siem.api

Class Confidencer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sailpoint.siem.api.Confidencer

  • public class Confidencer
extends java.lang.Object
    Author:
    adam.creaney (Created on 12/18/18). This class is intended to provide 'best guess' at which Identity is being requested, based on an account name that is passed to the SIEM endpoint. Most of the time this will be an all or nothing, with account names mapping to a single identity.

      • compareIdentitiesAndLinks

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Double> compareIdentitiesAndLinks()
                                                                           throws sailpoint.tools.GeneralException
        Function to compare the identity objects and the links to determine the 'confidence score' of each based on the other entries (eg. if one is really old and hasn't been updated in years, but one has been updated in the last few days, it is likely that the active one is of interest vs the inactive.
